    steps: ['Define clear, measurable evaluation dimensions (e.g., feasibility impact, social impact, spatial impact) before the project concludes .', 'Deploy a mix of assessment instruments: technical surveys, social surveys, observational forms, and material footprint tracking , .', 'Collect data from all involved actors across the different project levels (designers, end-users, city officials) .', 'Compile the findings into a formal evaluation matrix to determine if the intervention should be scaled, adjusted, or abandoned , .'],
