    d: ["spatial", "heritage"],
    def: 'Relevant to mathematically and visually test how a proposed physical change will alter the aesthetic and historical scenery of the city before a single brick is laid. — Computational 3D maps and cumulative visual profiles demonstrating exactly which parts of a historic landscape will remain visible, or become blocked, by a new development.',
