    d: ["spatial", "social"],
    def: 'Relevant to objectively measure local accessibility gaps, prioritizing interventions that bring essential daily services closer to residents\' doorsteps. — Visual proximity atlases and spatial analyses demonstrating whether residents can access education, healthcare, and fresh food within a 15-minute walk or cycle.',
