    steps: ['Aggregate base spatial data including terrain models, Building Information Models (BIM), and GIS layers.', 'Convert this structural data into an open, interoperable semantic format (like CityGML) to ensure long-term usability.', 'Link the static 3D model to live IoT sensor networks and municipal databases to create a bidirectional flow of information.', 'Use the platform to run specialized simulations (e.g., flood risks, traffic flow) and share the visualizations openly with citizens and planners for collaborative decision-making.'],
