    steps: ['Identify a specific regulatory barrier preventing a desired urban intervention (e.g., rules against community-managed energy or temporary street commerce).', 'Establish a "sandbox"—a defined physical area or specific policy domain where the standard regulations are temporarily suspended or modified by the municipality.', 'Run the urban intervention under these new, experimental rules in close collaboration with civic and private actors.', 'Monitor the legal, economic, and social impacts strictly; if successful, use this evidence to permanently rewrite the municipal bureaucratic procedures.'],
